25/10/2002
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The army chiefs of staff of Bulgaria, Romania, Greece and Turkey issued a joint statement Thursday (24 October) condemning the actions of Chechen rebels who are holding hundreds of people hostage in a Moscow theatre. 
Generals Nikola Kolev, Mihail Popescu, Georges Antonakopoulos and Hilmi Ozkok called for closer co-operation between states in combating new challenges to security and terrorism. 
They were meeting in Sofia ahead of NATO's Prague summit in support of Bulgaria and Romania's candidacies. 
(AFP, Seeurope - 24/10/02)
